<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-356-574  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 356 574.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  March 28 1990 n129 p101(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Intelligent backup. (Software Review) (Sterling SoftwareIntelligent Backup floppy-disk backup system) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fronteras, Adam.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Sterling Software's Intelligent Backup is a floppy disk backuputility that integrates a powerful file-handling system inaddition to comprehensive backup and restore utilities.andP;  Itcontains an install program that asks the user which drive anddrive type to back up to as well as other configuration questions.andO;The installation routine automatically edits AUTOEXEC.BAT andCONFIG.SYS to define backup parameters.andP;  Intelligent Backup canperform backups automatically at user-defined intervals bychecking the system clock.andP;  Users can restore by path, filename,or drive; sort directories, edit files, and delete files; ordelete directories.andP;  Intelligent Backup is rated an overall 'good'value as a well designed disk backup system for both experiencedand inexperienced users.Price is 150 pounds sterling.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sterling Software Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    SSW.andO;Product:   Intelligent Backup (Utility program).andO;Topic:     Back-Up SystemsDisk-Tape File UtilitiesSoftware PackagesFloppy DiskEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   User verdict. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Intelligent BackupandM;USER VERDICTandM;* PRODUCT NAME Intelligent BackupandM;* SUPPLIED BY Sterling Software, 64-78 Kingsway, London, WC2B 6AI.andP;  Tel: (01)528 8333andM;* DESCRIPTION Backup and file management system.andM;* PRICE 150 poundsandM;* PC USER VERDICT A good all round disk backup system for the experienced andinexperienced.andM;Tape streamers and networks are a luxury for small businesses; even in largesites you often find a great deal of single-user machines, particularly forword processing and spreadsheets.andP;  Giving each machines a tape streamer is anexpensive option and linking them into a network isn't always possible.andM;Getting users to back up using MS-DOS is a non-starter, since inexperiencedDOS users will find it almost impossible to use and not completely reliable.andO;This is particularly evident when restoring to different machines withdifferent versions of DOS.andP;  The other bugbear is the length of time it takes.andM;To overcome this, Sterling Software has released a floppy disk backup system.andO;Intelligent Backup has the additional bonus of containing a powerfulfile-handling system.andM;The package arrives with both 5-1/4 and 3-1/2-inch disks -- it's a pity morepackages don't arrive in dual format.andP;  Also included is a 90-page instructionmanual and a set of labels to stick on your backup disks.andM;The package contains an install program which asks you to confirm which driveyou'll be backing up to, type of disk drive and so on, making installationeasy.andP;  Intelligent Backup will then alter the AUTOEXEC and CONFIG files.andP;  Thepackage allows you to define where in the AUTOEXEC you want the IB.andP;  Mostusefully, it forces you to go back and alter the AUTOEXEC files to make surethe right order sequences are carried out.andM;This means that IB does a backup when the machine is switched on and a datecheck so that it's only done once a day.andP;  The first time IB does a backup itbacks up the whole PC; after that it backs up changed files and occasionallydoes reconciliation and full backups.andP;  The daily backup only takes a coupleof minutes.andM;Beyond the backup side are very comprehensive file and restore utilities.andO;You can restore by path, filename and full drives.andP;  The disk utilitiesinclude sorting directories, editing files and deletion by individual file ortagged files.andP;  Caution is advised in deleting directories as it's possible todelete whole and sub-directories with one delete command.andM;Yet, backup is only as good as the restore and here Intelligent Backupshines.andP;  Even when there was a faulty disk the restore utility recovered allexcept one small file where a normal DOS 'dir' command couldn't read thedisk.andP;  However, as with most backup software some copy protected softwarebacked up fine but wouldn't always restore--Lotus and Autoroute failed forinstance.andP;  Overall, Intelligent Backup proved a worthwhile program and ifyou're running without doing regular backups then this is a good investment.andO;</TEXT></DOC>